{"title_page": "Kriszti\u00e1n Vad\u00f3cz", "text_new": "{{Eastern name order|Vad\u00f3cz Kriszti\u00e1n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Kriszti\u00e1n Vad\u00f3cz\n| image = Kriszti\u00e1n Vad\u00f3cz.jpg\n| image_size = 250\n| caption = Vad\u00f3cz playing with [[Kitchee SC|Kitchee]] in 2017\n| fullname =\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1985|5|30|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Budapest]], Hungary\n| height = {{convert|1.88|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Pe\u00f1arol]]\n| clubnumber = 28\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Budapest Honv\u00e9d FC|Honv\u00e9d]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132005 | clubs1 = [[Budapest Honv\u00e9d FC|Honv\u00e9d]] | caps1 = 72 | goals1 = 7\n| years2 = 2005\u20132007 | clubs2 = [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre B]] | caps2 = 32 | goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2007 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]] (loan) | caps3 = 11 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2007\u20132008 | clubs4 = [[N.E.C. (football club)|NEC]] | caps4 = 28 | goals4 = 2\n| years5 = 2008\u20132011 | clubs5 = [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]] | caps5 = 71 | goals5 = 9\n| years6 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs6 = [[N.E.C. (football club)|NEC]] | caps6 = 29 | goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2012\u20132014 | clubs7 = [[Odense Boldklub|Odense]] | caps7 = 36 | goals7 = 9\n| years8 = 2014 | clubs8 = [[FC Pune City|Pune City]] | caps8 = 6 | goals8 = 0\n| years9 = 2015 | clubs9 = [[Grasshopper Club Z\u00fcrich|Grasshoppers]] | caps9 = 15 | goals9 = 2\n| years10 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs10 = [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s|Alav\u00e9s]] | caps10 = 3 | goals10 = 0\n| years11 = 2016 | clubs11 = [[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]] | caps11 = 11 | goals11 = 1\n| years12 = 2016 | clubs12 = [[Mumbai City FC|Mumbai City]] | caps12 = 14 | goals12 = 3\n| years13 = 2017\u20132018 | clubs13 = [[Kitchee SC|Kitchee]] | caps13 = 27 | goals13 = 10 \n| years14 = 2018 | clubs14 = [[Budapest Honv\u00e9d FC|Honv\u00e9d]] | caps14 = 6 | goals14 = 0 \n| years15 = 2018\u20132019 | clubs15 = [[Kitchee SC|Kitchee]] | caps15 = 13 | goals15 = 3\n| years16 = 2019 | clubs16 = [[Budapest Honv\u00e9d FC|Honv\u00e9d]] | caps16 = 11 | goals16 = 0\n| years17 = 2020\u2013 | clubs17 = [[Pe\u00f1arol]] | caps17 = 1 | goals17 = 0\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2004\u20132006 | nationalteam1 = [[Hungary national under-21 football team|Hungary U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 \n| nationalyears2 = 2004\u2013 | nationalteam2 = [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] | nationalcaps2 = 42 | nationalgoals2 = 2\n| club-update = 16 February 2020\n| nationalteam-update = 10 June 2018\n}}\n\n'''Kriszti\u00e1n Vad\u00f3cz''' ({{IPA-hu|\u02c8kristia\u02d0n \u02c8v\u0252do\u02d0t\u0361s|lang}}; born 30 May 1985) is a [[Hungary|Hungarian]] professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Uruguayan club [[Pe\u00f1arol]] as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Early years===\nBorn in [[Budapest]], Vad\u00f3cz made his professional debuts aged 17, with hometown's [[Budapest Honv\u00e9d FC]], and caught the eye of [[Ligue 1]] club [[AJ Auxerre]] in summer 2005. However, he managed no first-team appearances in a three-year spell, finishing his last on loan to [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]] in [[Scotland]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/m/motherwell/6315479.stm Hungarian agrees Well loan deal]; [[BBC Sport]], 31 January 2007</ref>\n\nIn June 2007, Vad\u00f3cz was finally released by the French, joining [[N.E.C. (football club)|NEC Nijmegen]]. During [[2007\u201308 Eredivisie|his only season]] in the [[Eredivisie]], he was an essential midfield element for a team that finished a comfortable eighth.\n\n===Osasuna===\nSubsequently, Vad\u00f3cz penned a four-year contract with [[CA Osasuna]].<ref>[https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/futbol/osasuna-ficha-al-medio-hungaro-krisztian-vadocz-5824799 Osasuna ficha al medio h\u00fangaro Krisztian Vadocz (Osasuna sign Hungarian midfielder Kristian Vadocz)]; [[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]], 11 August 2008 (in Spanish)</ref> Never an undisputed starter in [[2008\u201309 La Liga|his first season]] in [[La Liga]] he did score some important goals, against [[UD Almer\u00eda]] (3\u20131, after only playing one minute)<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/252827?cc=5739 Osasuna 3\u20131 Almeria]; [[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]], 23 November 2008</ref> and at [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] (4\u20132).<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/253069?cc=5739 Atl\u00e9tico Madrid 2\u20134 Osasuna]; ESPN Soccernet, 5 April 2009</ref>\n\nIn the [[2009\u201310 La Liga|2009\u201310 campaign]], Vad\u00f3cz appeared in exactly the same number of matches for the [[Navarre]]se, again mainly [[Substitute (association football)|from the bench]]. On 11 April 2010, he netted from 35 yards to help his team to a 2\u20130 home win against [[Real Zaragoza]].<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/275683?cc=5739 Osasuna prove too strong for Zaragoza]; ESPN Soccernet, 11 April 2010</ref>\n\n===Late career===\nVad\u00f3cz was released by Osasuna in the last day of the 2011 summer [[transfer window]], immediately signing with former side NEC. On 6 September 2012 he changed clubs and countries again, joining [[Odense Boldklub]] in the [[Danish Superliga]].<ref>[http://www.ob.dk/artikel/krisztin-vadcz-praesenteret-i-ob.aspx Kriszti\u00e1n Vad\u00f3cz pr\u00e6senteret i OB (Kriszti\u00e1n Vad\u00f3cz presented at OB)]; Odense Boldklub, 6 September 2012 (in Danish)</ref>\n\nOn 14 November 2014, Vad\u00f3cz moved to the [[Indian Super League]] with [[FC Pune City]], as an injury replacement to [[John Goossens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/sports/hungarian-krisztian-vadocz-replaces-injured-john-goossens-fc-pune-city-1803675.html|title=Hungarian Krisztian Vadocz replaces injured John Goossens at FC Pune City|publisher=[[Firstpost]]|date=14 November 2014|accessdate=14 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportskeeda.com/football/hungarian-vadocz-replaces-john-goossens-at-fc-pune-city|title=Former Osasuna midfielder Krisztian Vadocz joins FC Pune City replacing John Goossens|publisher=[[Sportskeeda]]|date=14 November 2014|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref> On 16 February of the following year, he was signed by [[Grasshopper Club Z\u00fcrich]] from the [[Swiss Super League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gcz.ch/news/gc-news/news/gc-verpflichtet-mittelfeldspieler-krisztian-vadocz/3649a7756a36beb455224ca4f11989a0/|title=GC verpflichtet mittelfeldspieler Krisztian Vadocz|trans-title=GC acquire midfielder Krisztian Vadocz|publisher=Grasshopper CZ|language=de|date=16 February 2015|accessdate=16 February 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150217020632/http://www.gcz.ch/news/gc-news/news/gc-verpflichtet-mittelfeldspieler-krisztian-vadocz/3649a7756a36beb455224ca4f11989a0/|archivedate=17 February 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/legiosok/grasshoppers-vadocz-a-27-szeres-svajci-bajnoknal-folytatja-2395293|title=Sv\u00e1jc: Vad\u00f3cz a 27-szeres bajnokcsapatn\u00e1l folytatja|trans-title=Switzerland: Vad\u00f3cz moves to 27-time champions|publisher=[[Nemzeti Sport]]|language=hu|date=16 February 2015|accessdate=16 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April 2015, Vad\u00f3cz scored twice against [[FC Sion]] to help to a 5\u20130 success at the [[Stade Tourbillon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gcz.ch/news/gc-news/news/50-sieg-im-tourbillon/f9dc0454a7fbdf2d52e55cb8bec34016/|title=5:0-Sieg im Tourbillon|trans-title=5:0-Win at Tourbillon|publisher=Grasshopper CZ|language=de|date=3 April 2015|accessdate=3 April 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150404214445/http://www.gcz.ch/news/gc-news/news/50-sieg-im-tourbillon/f9dc0454a7fbdf2d52e55cb8bec34016/|archivedate=4 April 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 19 September he moved back to Spain, after agreeing to a one-year deal with [[Deportivo Alav\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deportivoalaves.com/el-deportivo-alaves-se-refuerza-con-el-centrocampista-hungaro-vadocz/|title=El Deportivo Alav\u00e9s se refuerza con el centrocampista h\u00fangaro Vad\u00f3cz|trans-title=Deportivo Alav\u00e9s bolster with Hungarian midfielder Vad\u00f3cz|publisher=Deportivo Alav\u00e9s|language=es|date=19 September 2015|accessdate=19 September 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150919223813/http://www.deportivoalaves.com/el-deportivo-alaves-se-refuerza-con-el-centrocampista-hungaro-vadocz/|archivedate=19 September 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 January 2016, after appearing rarely for the [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basques]], Vad\u00f3cz terminated his contract and joined [[Perth Glory FC]] on an injury-replacement contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2016/01/28/segunda/1453978866_610613.html|title=Vadocz rescind\u00f3 con el Alav\u00e9s y se va al Perth australiano|trans-title=Vadocz terminated with Alav\u00e9s and goes to Australia's Perth|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=28 January 2016|accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref> At the end of [[2015\u201316 A-League|the season]], he was not offered a new deal and was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.a-league.com.au/article/perth-glory-reveal-squad-changes/1f2cuo6srjns2zkh1dk3i8qdx|title=Perth Glory reveal squad shake-up|publisher=[[Football Federation Australia]]|date=8 May 2016|accessdate=8 May 2016}}</ref>\n\nVad\u00f3cz signed for [[Mumbai City FC]] on 28 June 2016, thus returning to the Indian top division.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestatesman.com/news/sports/mumbai-fc-sign-krisztian-vadocz-gerson-vieira-for-isl-3/150905.html|title=Mumbai City FC sign Krisztian Vadocz, Gerson Vieira for ISL 3|publisher=[[The Statesman (India)|The Statesman]]|date=28 June 2016|accessdate=28 June 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011023401/http://www.thestatesman.com/news/sports/mumbai-fc-sign-krisztian-vadocz-gerson-vieira-for-isl-3/150905.html|archivedate=11 October 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Hong Kong Premier League]]'s [[Kitchee SC]] announced his signing for six months the following 11 January,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kitchee.com/news.php?id=505|title=\u5091\u5fd7\u518d\u7c3d\u5165\u570b\u5bb6\u968a\u6210\u54e1 \u92b3\u610f\u6311\u6230\u4e9e\u51a0\u76c3|trans-title=|publisher=Kitchee SC|language=zh|date=11 January 2017|accessdate=29 January 2017}}</ref> and on 8 June the 32-year-old renewed his contract with the latter until the end of the [[2017\u201318 Hong Kong Premier League|2017\u201318 campaign]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kitchee.com/news.php?id=557|title=\u5091\u5fd7\u8207\u524d\u5308\u7259\u5229\u570b\u8173\u83ef\u675c\u65af\u7e8c\u7d04\u4e00\u5e74|trans-title=|publisher=Kitchee SC|language=zh|date=8 June 2017|accessdate=18 June 2017}}</ref> where he won the Hong Kong Footballer of the Year, Players\u2019 Player of the Year, Most Favourite Player and Top Midfielder awards.<ref name=FOTY>{{cite news|url=http://www.scmp.com/sport/hong-kong/article/2146646/emotional-krisztian-vadocz-scoops-four-awards-hong-kong-top|title=I\u2019m not crying, but it\u2019s emotional: Kitchee\u2019s Krisztian Vadocz scoops four at Hong Kong Top Footballer Awards|publisher=[[South China Morning Post]]|date=17 May 2018|accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nVad\u00f3cz returned to his native Hungary on 5 July 2018, agreeing to a one-year deal with Honv\u00e9d.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/honved-vadocz-krisztian-visszater-kispestre-hivatalos-2645545|title=Honv\u00e9d: Vad\u00f3cz Kriszti\u00e1n visszat\u00e9r Kispestre \u2013 hivatalos|trans-title=Honv\u00e9d: Kriszti\u00e1n Vad\u00f3cz returns to Kispest \u2013 official|publisher=Nemzeti Sport|language=hu|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref> On 28 August, however, he terminated his contract by mutual consent because he opted to continue to play abroad.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/honved-vadocz-krisztian-maris-tavozik-a-klubtol-hivatalos-2655109|title=Honv\u00e9d: Vad\u00f3cz Kriszti\u00e1n m\u00e1ris t\u00e1vozik a klubt\u00f3l \u2013 hivatalos|trans-title=Honv\u00e9d: Kriszti\u00e1n Vad\u00f3cz leaves the club \u2013 official|publisher=Nemzeti Sport|language=hu|date=28 August 2018|accessdate=28 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nVad\u00f3cz returned to Kitchee on 17 October 2018, with head coach [[Chu Chi Kwong]] confirming that the player had signed a multi-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.mingpao.com/ins/instantnews/web_tc/article/20181017/s00006/1539762499344|title=\u6e2f\u8db3\u5148\u751f\u83ef\u675c\u65af\u56de\u6b78\u3000\u91cd\u8fd4\u5091\u5fd7\u52a9\u62f3\u722d\u4e0a\u524d\u5217|trans-title=Hong Kong Footballer of the Year Vad\u00f3cz returns to return to the top|publisher=[[Ming Pao]]|language=zh|date=17 October 2018|accessdate=17 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E9%AB%94%E8%82%B2/248440/%E6%B8%AF%E8%B6%85%E8%81%AF-%E8%8F%AF%E6%9D%9C%E6%96%AF%E6%94%BE%E4%B8%8B%E5%8E%BB%E5%AD%A3%E5%85%89%E7%92%B0-%E5%88%9D%E8%A1%B7%E4%B9%8B%E5%BF%83%E7%9B%BC%E5%86%8D%E9%A0%98%E5%82%91%E5%BF%97%E8%A1%9D%E5%86%A0|title=\u83ef\u675c\u65af\u653e\u4e0b\u53bb\u5b63\u5149\u74b0\u3000\u521d\u8877\u4e4b\u5fc3\u76fc\u518d\u9818\u5091\u5fd7\u885d\u51a0|trans-title=|publisher=HK 01|last=Yuen|first=Chi Ho|language=zh|date=17 October 2018|accessdate=18 October 2018}}</ref> The following 27 August, he left.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E9%AB%94%E8%82%B2/368635/%E6%B8%AF%E8%B6%85%E8%81%AF-%E5%82%91%E5%BF%97%E5%85%AC%E5%B8%83%E5%A4%96%E6%8F%B4%E5%90%8D%E5%96%AE-%E4%B8%AD%E5%A0%B4%E5%A4%A7%E5%B0%87%E9%9B%A2%E9%9A%8A-%E5%9C%96%E8%AA%AA%E8%8F%AF%E6%9D%9C%E6%96%AF%E5%9C%A8%E6%B8%AF%E7%94%9F%E6%B6%AF|title=\u5091\u5fd7\u516c\u5e03\u5916\u63f4\u540d\u55ae\u3000\u4e2d\u5834\u5927\u5c07\u96e2\u968a\u3000\u5716\u8aaa\u83ef\u675c\u65af\u5728\u6e2f\u751f\u6daf|trans-title=|publisher=HK 01|last=Yuen|first=Chi Ho|language=zh|date=27 August 2019|accessdate=27 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter a half year at Honv\u00e9d, Vad\u00f3cz joined [[Pe\u00f1arol]] of the [[Uruguayan Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] on 4 January 2020, where he was reunited with former Mumbai City teammate [[Diego Forl\u00e1n]] who acted as manager of the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.futbol.com.uy/Deportes/Penarol--Si-te-llama-Diego-Forlan-no-podes-decirle-que-no--dijo-Krisztian-Vadocz-uc740271|title=Pe\u00f1arol: \u201cSi te llama Diego Forl\u00e1n no pod\u00e9s decirle que no\u201d, dijo Krisztian Vad\u00f3cz|trans-title=Pe\u00f1arol: \u201cIf Diego Forl\u00e1n calls you you can't say no\u201d, said Krisztian Vad\u00f3cz|publisher=F\u00fatbol Uruguay|language=es|date=4 January 2020|accessdate=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nVad\u00f3cz made his debut for both [[Hungary national under-21 football team|Hungary's under-21]] and [[Hungary national football team|the full side]] in 2004. He scored his first goal for the latter a year later, in a 3\u20130 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] win over [[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]] in [[Miami, Florida]].\n\n===International goals===\n(Hungary score listed first, score column indicates score after each Vad\u00f3cz goal)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=25960|title=Vad\u00f3cz Kriszti\u00e1n|publisher=European Football|accessdate=12 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n! No !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 18 December 2005 || [[Riccardo Silva Stadium|Riccardo Silva]], [[Miami]], [[United States]] || {{fb|ATG}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20130 || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 2. || 24 May 2008 || [[Pusk\u00e1s Ferenc Stadion (1953)|Ferenc Pusk\u00e1s]], [[Budapest]], Hungary || {{fb|GRE}} || 