itle: ''Quelqu'un derri\u00e8re la porte''\n|-\n| 1971 || ''[[Ten Days' Wonder (film)|Ten Days' Wonder]]'' || Charles Van Horn || Original French title: ''La D\u00e9cade prodigieuse''\n|-\n| 1972 || ''[[Play It as It Lays (film)|Play It as It Lays]]'' || B.Z. Mendenhall ||\n|-\n| 1972 || ''[[The Life and Times of Judge Roy Bean]]'' || Reverend LaSalle ||\n|-\n| 1973 || ''[[The Last of Sheila]]'' || N/A || Co-writer with [[Stephen Sondheim]]<br />[[List of Edgar Allan Poe Award for Best Motion Picture Screenplay winners|Edgar Allan Poe Award for Best Motion Picture Screenplay]]\n|-\n| 1974 || ''[[Lovin' Molly]]'' || Gid Frye ||\n|-\n| 1974 || ''[[Murder on the Orient Express (1974 film)|Murder on the Orient Express]]'' || Hector McQueen ||\n|-\n| 1975 || ''[[Mahogany (film)|Mahogany]]'' || Sean McAvoy ||\n|-\n| 1978 || ''[[Remember My Name]]'' || Neil Curry ||\n|-\n| 1979 || ''[[Winter Kills (film)|Winter Kills]]'' || John Cerruti ||\n|-\n| 1979 || ''Twice a Woman'' || Alfred Boeken || Original Dutch title: ''Twee Vrouwen''\n|-\n| 1979 || ''[[The Black Hole]]'' || Dr. Alex Durant ||\n|-\n| 1980 || ''[[North Sea Hijack]]'' || Lou Kramer || Alternate titles: ''ffolkes'' and ''Assault Force''\n|-\n| 1980 || ''[[Deadly Companion]]'' || Lawrence Miles || Alternate title: ''Double Negative''\n|-\n| 1983 || ''[[Psycho II (film)|Psycho II]]'' || [[Norman Bates]] ||\n|-\n| 1984 || ''[[Crimes of Passion (1984 film)|Crimes of Passion]]'' || Reverend Peter Shayne ||\n|-\n| 1986 || ''[[Psycho III]]'' || [[Norman Bates]] || Also director<br />Nominated \u2013 [[Saturn Award for Best Actor]]\n|-\n| 1988 || ''[[Destroyer (1988 film)|Destroyer]]'' || Robert Edwards || Alternate title: ''Shadow of Death''\n|-\n| 1988 || ''[[Lucky Stiff (film)|Lucky Stiff]]'' || N/A || Director\n|-\n| 1989 || ''[[Edge of Sanity (film)|Edge of Sanity]]'' || [[Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde (character)|Dr. Henry Jekyll]] / [[Jack the Ripper|Jack \"The Ripper\" Hyde]] ||\n|-\n| 1991 || ''[[A Demon in My View]]''